just_use games.go

# label: WORKHORSE
# role: encodes domain knowledge

Game Lobby Host. Metaphor: host holds the phone for a remote player —
relays events faithfully, doesn't know the rules. Rule enforcement
delegates to a game-specific referee (lynrummy.CheckEvent). Games, host,
referee stay separate so a new game type only adds a referee.

Game creation is one round trip: client posts a shuffled 104-card deck,
Dealer deals, the GameSetup "photo" becomes the first game_events row, and
the response carries it back. Every subsequent event replays against this
setup — ReconstructBoard in the referee is how the host gets the "current
board" to hand the rule-checker.

Long-poll via per-game waiters map (game_id → []chan). notifyWaiters
closes each channel on every new event; waiters re-query rather than
receiving the event directly.
